    }
  ],
  "cards": [
    {
      "id": "intro-0",
      "sectionId": "intro",
      "title": "Intro",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "This quick reference cheat sheet provides various for using SSH."
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-1",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "Connect to a server (default port 22)"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-2",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "```shell script\n$ ssh root@192.168.1.5"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-3",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nConnect on a specific port"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-4",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh root@192.168.1.5 -p 6222"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-5",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nConnect via pem file (0400 permissions)"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-6",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh -i /path/file.pem root@192.168.1.5"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-7",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nSee: [SSH Permissions](/chmod#ssh-permissions)\n\n### Executing\n\nExecutes remote command"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-8",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh root@192.168.1.5 'ls -l'"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-9",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nInvoke a local script"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-10",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh root@192.168.1.5 bash < script.sh"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-11",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nCompresses and downloads from a server"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-12",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh root@192.168.1.5 \"tar cvzf - ~/source\" > output.tgz"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-13",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n### SCP {.row-span-2}\n\nCopies from remote to local"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-14",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ scp user@server:/dir/file.ext dest/"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-15",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nCopies between two servers"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-16",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ scp user@server:/file user@server:/dir"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-17",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nCopies from local to remote"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-18",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ scp dest/file.ext user@server:/dir"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-19",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nCopies a whole folder"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-20",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ scp -r user@server:/dir dest/"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-21",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nCopies all files from a folder"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-22",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ scp user@server:/dir/* dest/"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-23",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nCopies from a server folder to the current folder"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-24",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ scp user@server:/dir/* ."
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-25",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n### Config location\n\n| File Path                | Description          |\n| ------------------------ | -------------------- |\n| `/etc/ssh/ssh_config`    | System-wide config   |\n| `~/.ssh/config`          | User-specific config |\n| `~/.ssh/id_{type}`       | Private key          |\n| `~/.ssh/id_{type}.pub`   | Public key           |\n| `~/.ssh/known_hosts`     | Known Servers        |\n| `~/.ssh/authorized_keys` | Authorized login key |\n\n### SCP Options\n\n| Options       | Description                                    |\n| ------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |\n| scp `-r`      | <yel>R</yel>ecursively copy entire directories |\n| scp `-C`      | <yel>C</yel>ompresses data                     |\n| scp `-v`      | Prints <yel>v</yel>erbose info                 |\n| scp `-P` 8080 | Uses a specific <yel>P</yel>ort                |\n| scp `-B`      | <yel>B</yel>atch mode _(Prevents password)_    |\n| scp `-p`      | <yel>P</yel>reserves times and modes           |\n\n### Config sample"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-26",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "Host server1\nHostName 192.168.1.5\nUser root\nPort 22\nIdentityFile ~/.ssh/server1.key"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-27",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nLaunch by alias"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-28",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh server1"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-29",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nSee: Full [Config Options](https://linux.die.net/man/5/ssh_config)\n\n### ProxyJump"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-30",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh -J proxy_host1 remote_host2"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-31",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh -J user@proxy_host1 user@remote_host2"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-32",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nMultiple jumps"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-33",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh -J user@proxy_host1:port1,user@proxy_host2:port2 user@remote_host3"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-34",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n### ssh-copy-id"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-35",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh-copy-id user@server"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-36",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nCopy to alias server"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-37",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh-copy-id server1"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-38",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nCopy specific key"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-39",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub user@server"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-40",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n## SSH keygen {.cols-5}\n\n### ssh-keygen {.col-span-2}"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-41",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C \"your@mail.com\""
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-42",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n---\n\n| -   | -    | -                             |\n| --- | ---- | ----------------------------- |\n|     | `-t` | [Type](#key-type) of key      |\n|     | `-b` | The number of bits in the key |\n|     | `-C` | Provides a new comment        |\n\n{.left-text}\n\nGenerate an RSA 4096 bit key with email as a comment\n\n### Generate {.col-span-2 .row-span-2}\n\nGenerate a key interactively"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-43",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh-keygen"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-44",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nSpecify filename"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-45",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh-keygen -f ~/.ssh/filename"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-46",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nGenerate public key from private key"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-47",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh-keygen -y -f private.key > public.pub"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-48",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nChange comment"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-49",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh-keygen -c -f ~/.ssh/id_rsa"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-50",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nChange private key passphrase"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-51",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh-keygen -p -f ~/.ssh/id_rsa"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-52",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n### Key type\n\n- rsa\n- ed25519\n- dsa\n- ecdsa\n\n### known_hosts {.col-span-2}\n\nSearch from known_hosts"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-53",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh-keygen -F <ip/hostname>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-54",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nRemove from known_hosts"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-55",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "$ ssh-keygen -R <ip/hostname>"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-56",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Connecting",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n### Key format\n\n- PEM\n- PKCS8\n\n## SSH Tunneling\n\n### SSH Tunnel Options {.row-span-2}\n\n| Option | Description                                            |\n| ------ | :----------------------------------------------------- |\n| `-L`   | Local port forwarding                                  |\n| `-R`   | Remote port forwarding                                 |\n| `-D`   | Dynamic port forwarding                                |\n| `-f`   | Run in background                                      |\n| `-N`   | Do not execute a remote command                        |\n| `-g`   | Allow remote hosts to connect to local forwarded ports |\n\n{.left-text}\n\nmore details on flag above with `man ssh`\n\n### Local Port Forwarding {.col-span-2}"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-57",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Getting Started",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "ssh -L local_port:remote_host:remote_port user@ssh_server"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-58",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Getting Started",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "ssh -L 8080:example.com:80 user@ssh_server"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-59",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Getting Started",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n### Dynamic Port Forwarding {.col-span-2}"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-60",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Getting Started",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "ssh -D local_port user@ssh_server"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-61",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Getting Started",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "ssh -f -N -D 1080 user@ssh_server"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-62",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Getting Started",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n### Background Tunnel {.col-span-3}"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-63",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Getting Started",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "ssh -f -N -L local_port:remote_host:remote_port user@ssh_server"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-64",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Getting Started",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n### Multiple Tunnels {.col-span-3}"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-65",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Getting Started",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "ssh -L 8080:example.com:80 -L 3306:db.example.com:3306 user@ssh_server"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-66",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Getting Started",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n### Combining Options {.col-span-3}"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-67",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Getting Started",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "ssh -f -N -g -L 8080:example.com:80 -i ~/.ssh/custom_key user@ssh_server"
    },
    {
      "id": "s1-68",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Getting Started",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n## Also see\n\n- [OpenSSH Config File Examples](https://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/create-ssh-config-file-on-linux-unix/) _(cyberciti.biz)_\n- [ssh_config](https://linux.die.net/man/5/ssh_config) _(linux.die.net)_\n- [man-ssh](https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man1/ssh.1.html)"
    }
  ],
